'''Abdulla Muaz''' is a Maldivian film actor.
==Career== Muaz made a brief appearance in [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]] directed horror film ''[[Edhathuru]]'' (2005) which revolves around eight friends who go on a picnic to a haunted uninhabited island and their battle for survival.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/111827 |title=Soba returning to screen with "Kaaku?" |work=Sun |language=Divehi |last=Musthafa |first=Mohamed |date=19 November 2018 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/uvxNQ |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=Edhathuru>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/18535 |title=Kuda Hajja will always be a star though she fails to fulfill her dreams |work=Avas |language=Divehi |last=Maaha |first=Aishath |date=13 June 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130061630/https://avas.mv/18535 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film garnered critical appreciation specially for its sound effect and was a commercial success.<ref name=GFA4won>{{cite news|url=https://haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/news/56402 |title="Vehey Vaarey Thereyn" lifts Best Film Award with six other awards |work=Avas |language=Divehi |last=Ahmed |first=Fazeena |date=20 December 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130062142/http://webcache.dhivehi.mv/haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/news/56402 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
