Moomin Fuad and Ali Shifau's critically appreciated crime film ''[[Heylaa (film)|Heylaa]]'' (2006) featured Muaz as a [[drug user]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://dho.mv/baiscope/44005 |title=Fuad regrets his involvement in Happy Birthday |language=Divehi |work=Dho? |last=Maaha |first=Aishath |date=21 October 2018 |archiveurl=http://archive.fo/0U4IL |deadurl=no |archivedate=17 January 2019 |accessdate=17 January 2019 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film narrates the story of a fourteen years old ambitious boy who finds himself unknowingly being involved in smuggling of a revolver.<ref name=DRE11years/> It was the first Maldivian film to be shot in high-definition digital video.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://inaamu.presidencymaldives.gov.mv/Index.aspx?lid=177&wid=1343 |title=Gaumee Inaam 2018 - Ali Shifau |work=Presidency Maldives |language=Divehi |archiveurl=http://archive.fo/8kp79 |deadurl=no |archivedate=3 December 2018 |accessdate=3 December 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Though the film received positive reviews from critics, it was a commercial failure.<ref name=DRE11years>{{cite news|url=https://dho.mv/baiscope/23701 |title=11 years anniversary for DRE; what did they achieve? |language=dv|work=Dho |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=14 September 2017 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/3d8z7 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=18 September 2018 |accessdate=18 September 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=Moomin>{{cite news|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/entertainment/107034 |title=Moomin not satisfied even after 12 Awards |language=Divehi |work=Haveeru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=4 July 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181216101531/https://archive.mv/dv/articles/DZ2eg |deadurl=yes |archivedate=16 December 2018 |accessdate=16 December 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Co-director of the film Shifau opined that its commercial status was a result of casting "not very prominent" faces in the film and the "film-goers were not ready to accept the genre" at the time of release.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sun.mv/109020 |title=Chippe with new hopes after receiving National Award |language=Divehi |work=Sun |last=Luba |first=Aminath |date=8 August 2018 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/aLZ95 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=16 December 2018 |accessdate=16 December 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Ahmed Nadheem from ''[[Haveeru Daily|Haveeru]]'' praised the narration and plot of the film while calling his performance to be "strictly average".<ref name=Heylaa>{{cite news|url=https://archive.mv/dv/articles/X9owd |title=Heylaa: An awakening film from a drowsed industry |language=Divehi |work=Haveeru |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=29 March 2012 |archiveurl=http://archive.fo/PReZ1 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=16 December 2018 |accessdate=16 December 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He next appeared as a man practicing the art of palmistry in ''[[Hukuru Vileyrey]]'' (2006), co-directed by [[Aishath Rishmy]] and [[Aminath Rasheedha]] which was based on a novel published by Ibrahim Waheed on ''[[Haveeru Daily]]'' in 2003.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/entertainment/35543 |title=Hukuru Vileyrey - Big hopes, big challenges: Ainthu |publisher=''Haveeru Daily'' |author=Naseer, Ismail |language=Divehi|date=20 July 2006 |accessdate=8 October 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name=HukuruVileyrey>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/17899 |title=Can "Vishka" be the movie of the year? |language=Divehi|publisher=''Avas'' |author=Nadheem, Ahmed |date=30 May 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603155311/https://avas.mv/17899 |archivedate=3 June 2016 |accessdate=3 June 2016}}</ref> The film was a critical and commercial success while being considered as "one of the few acceptable horror film the Maldivian Film Industry has ever produced".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/entertainment/31025 |title=Fanaa: Proof of Yaaraa‚Äôs immaturity |publisher=''Haveeru Daily'' |author=Naafiz, Ali |date=19 July 2010 |accessdate=8 October 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://dho.mv/style/30663 |title=Rishmy's style prior to Red Carpet |language=Divehi |work=Dho? |last=Rasheed |first=Nurah |date=8 February 2018 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/4YtMe |deadurl=no |archivedate=18 January 2019 |accessdate=18 January 2019 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was later released as 15 episodes television series with inclusion of several clips that were edited off while released in theatre.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/entertainment/49056 |title="Hukuru Vileyrey" releasing as a Drama |publisher=''Haveeru Daily'' |author=Ahmed, Fazeena |language=Divehi|date=23 November 2006 |accessdate=8 October 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://vnews.mv/103080 |title=Isn't Azza the greatest? |language=Divehi |work=VNews |last=Shaneeza |first=Mariyam |date=11 September 2018 |archiveurl=http://archive.fo/iYhNe |deadurl=no |archivedate=18 January 2019 |accessdate=18 January 2019 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
Muaz officially made his film debut in a leading role with [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]]-directed ''[[Hiyy Rohvaanulaa]]'' which features Shafeeu, [[Niuma Mohamed]] and [[Nadhiya Hassan]] alongside him.<ref name=HiyyRohvaanulaa>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/index.php/entertainment/25099 |title=Are these stars fallen? |work=Mihaaru |language=Divehi |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=17 October 2017 |archiveurl=http://archive.vn/n9hbp |deadurl=no |archivedate=4 January 2019 |accessdate=4 January 2019 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film follows a blind man who regains his eyesight but decides to fake his blindness to discover her wife's affair with another man.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/12282|title=A festival of Amjey's films to be organized |language=Divehi|work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=30 January 2017 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/4lsJZ |deadurl=no |archivedate=22 December 2018 |accessdate=22 December 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Muaz played the role of Vishal, a ruthless and determined man who is ready to go extreme extent to win back his first love.<ref name=HiyyRohvaanulaa/> The film received favorable reviews from critics and was a commercial success.
